            . I was sent for and took the prisoner - she wanted to go on her knees to beg pardon, and said she did it from want.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I asked the price before the shopman came round.</p>
               <p>GEORGE MACKAY. No, she did not till I seized her; it was close under her shawl.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that the gown had fallen down at her feet, and she had merely taken it up.</p>
